  • Are.na / About
  • https://hyp.is/xAFKkAIlEeuvDQPmd-lVDg/www.are.na/about
  • An Open Source Tool for Thinking Together
  • Weaving Social Network connecting Networked Thoughts, Resources, and Ideas organized into Channels for discovery, sharing, and collaboration
  • When you create a channel you can see if there are any related channels out there and if they are open you can just add your bit there
  • A Pinterest Clone and Collaborative Tool for Thought
  •  SaaS

-  video  : Getting Started with Are.na on Vimeo
  • connecting content and explore the community
  • Think of a channel 
    • as a place where you can layout
    • everything related to an idea
  • that may 
    • research, inspiration, photos, notes
  • drag anything to your channel
  • all appear in a neatly arranged in a grid
  • Add block
    • paste links to add web pages
    • type directly in the box to add a note
  • To save content as you browse the web you 
    • install the are.na Chrome Extension
    • Are.na - Chrome Web Store 10k+ users

- image credit : Building-A-Second-Brain - Fernando Gros

  • The way we conceptualize a thing, the way we articulate our tacit awareness of it
  • designates the implicate associative complex 
  • from which it arose
  • fixes the space of possibilities for it.
  • In this particular it implicates commitment to views such as
    • The Brain is the seat of Intelligence, Intellect consciousness
    • It is a discrete self-standing unit of material
    • It emphasizes utility as it affords better productivity and effectiveness of or recall, organization of thoughts, ideas, intents

- contrast with : ExtTelligence

- contrast with : ExteLect
  • Externalize Intellect
  • commitments
    • Intellect as a non-material thing
    • granted reality beyond being tied down to specific manifestation
    • By definition it exists in mutual arising with Collective Intellect
    • Intelligence is a narrower utilitarian concept

content.html:
- venue : FlowShow 07 Sept


- outline :
  • internet agents/humans communicate
    • The whole point of the Internet is to have agents/humans communicate with agents/humans. #h
    • On the Web primary agency is granted to
      • Web sites
        • address by location, perfect for centralized control
        • silos of data, capabilities
        • The network effect benefits the platforms aggregators not the creators of content
      • where People flock to
    • Flip that Put Humans First as articulated by Rushkoff and Jarnier
      • Give them Primary Agency
        • ability to address by content or person
        • trust but verify
        • unenclosable carriers
        • uncensorable
        • with strong privacy guarantees
        • but at the same time boundless attributed sharing and collaboration
      • Develop technology for human ends not to end Human

    • Semantic Web
      • empowering machines and corporations making use of these machines
      • to make use of content created by humans for humans
      • to extract value from the only source that is people
    • Even Holochain the champion of unenclosability busying itself to process agent-centric agreement and consensus in a p2p network instead of creating  people-centric networked conversation that facilitate experimenting, bootstraping, co-evolving putitive approaches collaboratively on the go. #h
  • Human First Architecture
    • Give Agency to Humans over their digital lives and communications
      • Empower the weavers of the network Human participants primarily to benefit from the emergent network effects
      • Build trust first
        • based on human rapport
      • Involve people in co-design, co-creation, collaboration
    • On the Architecture side Build 
      • promote conversations that are continuous without being asynchronous
      • give people vehicles for sense making, to understand and to be understood
      • Let them use capabilities afford personal sweet spots for them while maintining boundless interoperability and agency
      • - play : video-Dream_Matthew_Charles.mp4
      • Technologically it requires unenclosable channels and capabilities
        • peer to peer communication
        • every participants to be their own hub in 
        • an emergent network people and content
        • Guarantee Sovereignity for people
          • over their own data 
            • available off line first 
            • share under their own terms and control
          • self-sovereign, self-administered identity
          • pseudonymous if need be or even anonymous
      • WebNative Technology Stack
        • What if the only thing you need is a browser
        • no plugins
        • zero install
        • work on  users' devices
        • even off line
        • Progressive Web Apps
        • Instead of Platforms
        • Let people act as autonomous sovereign agents
        • use constellation providers like fission
        • and Personal constellation providers like TrailHub
      • Beyond Interoperability
        • Discoverability
        • Tinkerability
        • Personalizability
        • Go Meta: articulate the means needed to improve articulation and augmenting the intellectual effectiveness of the individual human being first
        • Bootstrap, co-create, co-evolve
  • Transcend documents, centralized scholarly publishing & flourish
    • Personalized mobile computing
    • Emergent Knowledge Federation
    • A Practical Framework for Augmenting Human Intellect
    • and improving Collective IQ
  • The very use of the phrase Artificial Intelligence is skewed in favor of machines
    • You could not talk sensibly about Machine Intellect
    • that is palpable non sense 
    • You could not build an academic disciple let alone an industry
    • This makes the anti human tendency of the dominant anti-ethos visible

content.html:
Just remembered. I worked on Computer Supported Collaborative Work in Virtual Environment 25 years ago. Designed and built a Display Metafor Scipting Language (a domain specific little language) with David Morris and implemented it with PCCTS, better known as ANTLR later, using data from LDAP and pumping HTML and Virtual Reality Markup Language to the Web.

Silicon Graphics machines were a thing then. Data stored in a distributed directory, LDAP. Tweeted

Morris D T, Lajos G, Dew P M, Drew R S and Willows D: ‘DiMe: An object oriented scripting language for the automatic creation of virtual environments’, in Proceedings of Eurographics, UK Chapter Conference (April 1997).

Mike Swaby Thesis 1998
